<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 02 at 1:33PM EST  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Lake Effect Snow Showers This Afternoon...
A band of lake effect snow will move across northern Lake County
in northwest Indiana through mid afternoon and then is expected to
shift east into Porter County later this afternoon. Visibilities
may briefly drop below one mile and localized snow accumulations
of 1 to 2 inches will be possible. Motorists should reduce speed
and allow extra traveling distance in this band of lake effect
snow.</description>
